gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Jazz 114, Pelicans 112
gameRecap.excerpt: Brandon Ingram missed a potential game-tying shot as the Utah Jazz hold on to a 114-112 victory over the Pelicans. Keyonte George led the Jazz with a career-high 19 points, along with five rebounds and three assists as Jordan Clarkson totaled 16 points and a season-high 10 assists. Zion Williamson (26 points, seven assists, four rebounds) and Brandon Ingram (25 points, five assists, four rebounds) led the Pelicans in the loss. The Jazz improve to 6-11 as the Pelicans move to 9-9.
